Class FeedSynchronizationItem

Represents the information required for synchronization of syndication feeds.

Syntax
[Serializable]
public class FeedSynchronizationItem : IComparable
Remarks

The FeedSynchronizationItem class represents a sx:sync element in the FeedSync specification.

This is required of all items in all feeds wishing to participate in FeedSync-based synchronization. Since FeedSynchronizationSharingInformation is not required, feed consumers must consider the presence of FeedSynchronizationItem in items or entries as an indication that the feed contains sync data.

It acceptable for a feed to have some items or entries with FeedSynchronizationItem elements, and some without a FeedSynchronizationItem. Only the items and entries that include the FeedSynchronizationItem element participate in FeedSync synchronization.

ConflictPreservation

Gets or sets a value indicating whether conflict preservation is performed for this item.

Declaration
public FeedSynchronizationConflictPreservationDirective ConflictPreservation { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
FeedSynchronizationConflictPreservationDirective

A FeedSynchronizationConflictPreservationDirective enumeration value that indicates whether conflict preservation is performed for this item. The default value is None, which indicates conflict preservation must be performed for the item.
Remarks

This value must only be set once, and shall only be set when the updates property value is 1. All updates to the item after the first update must propagate whatever state was set on the first update.

Within this framework, Ignore is equivalent to true for the noconflicts attribute in the FeedSync specification, while Perform is equivalent to false for the noconflicts attribute in the FeedSync specification. Specifying a value of None is equivalent to the noconflicts attribute not being present.

Id

Gets or sets the globally unique identifier for this item.

Declaration
public string Id { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

The globally unique identifier for this item.
Remarks

The Id must be globally unique within the feed and it must be identical across feeds if an item is being shared or synchronized as part of multiple distinct independent feeds.

Atom has a similar requirement for each entry to have a unique id. While the Atom entry id could be used for the sync id at the publisher’s discretion, implementers must not assume that the Atom id for the entry matches the sync id. Likewise, if the RSS item includes a guid, implementers must not assume that the guid is the same as the sync id.

In Atom feeds, it is acceptable to have multiple entries in the same feed with the same atom id element; in this case, the entries are considered different versions of the same entry. It is allowed to use FeedSync in such a feed, but the sx:sync/@id attributes are still required to be different in each entry. FeedSync considers those entries to be different sync items.

The Id is assigned by the creator of the item, and must not be changed by subsequent publishers. Applications will collate and compare these identifiers; therefore they must conform to the syntax for Namespace Specific Strings (the NSS portion of a URN) in RFC 2141.

Type Condition
System.ArgumentNullException

The value is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

FeedSynchronizationTombstoneStatus

A FeedSynchronizationTombstoneStatus enumeration value that indicates whether this item has been deleted. The default value is None, which indicates the item has not been deleted.
Remarks

Within this framework, Deleted is equivalent to true for the deleted attribute in the FeedSync specification, while Present is equivalent to false for the deleted attribute in the FeedSync specification. Specifying a value of None is equivalent to the deleted attribute not being present.

Returns
Type Description
System.Int32

A 32-bit signed integer indicating the lexical relationship between the two comparands.
Remarks

If the collections contain the same number of elements, determines the lexical relationship between the two sequences of comparands.

If the source has an element count that is greater than the target element count, returns 1.

If the source has an element count that is less than the target element count, returns -1.
